Port Shepstone SAPS detectives are investigating a case of attempted murder after a 22-year-old was run over twice - by his friends. The incident took place in Marburg, Port Shepstone, over the weekend. According to Port Shepstone police spokesperson Captain Petros Mpinge, two people aged 24 and 35 were arrested on Monday and will appear at the Port Shepstone Magistrate’s Court for the attack. “The victim (22) was taken to a local hospital and is in a critical condition,” said Mpinge, adding that both suspects are being held in police custody pending their court appearance. “Their bail application will be on [Tuesday] January 19 at the Port Shepstone Magistrate’s Court,” said Mpinge.